text: John Stewart (died 1769), of Castle Stewart, Wigtownshire, was a Scottish politician. He was a Member (MP) for Wigtownshire in 1747–1754. ==References== Category:Year of birth missing Category:1769 deaths Category:18th-century Scottish people Category:People from Dumfries and Galloway Category:Members of the Parliament of Great Britain for Scottish constituencies Category:British MPs 1747–1754
